Script,FoundEndplay
window.currentPBSScenario = 'FoundEndplay';
window.currentPBSScenarioFilename = 'Found_Endplay';
console.log('PBS: Logging scenario selection for FoundEndplay');
fetch('https://bba.harmonicsystems.com/api/scenario/select', {
    method: 'POST',
    headers: {
        'Content-Type': 'application/json',
        'X-Client-Version': '1.0.0'
    },
    body: JSON.stringify({
        scenario: 'FoundEndplay',
        user: whoAmI() || 'anonymous'
    })
}).then(function(r){ console.log('PBS: Server response', r.status); }).catch(function(e){ console.log('PBS: Fetch error', e); });
setDealerCode(`

/*
convention-card-ns: Basic-Bridge
convention-card-ew: Basic-Bridge
auction-filter: Auction.....
*/
# bba-direct: true
# auction-filter: Auction.....
# convention-card-ns: Basic-Bridge
# convention-card-ew: Basic-Bridge

action printoneline,
`, "S", true)
Script
Button,Found Endplay,\n\
--- Found Endplays (4!H / 4!S) — curated strip-and-endplay candidates\n\
\n\
These hands are scanned from all bba/*.pbn files by\n\
[find_endplay_candidates.py]: South declares a 4-of-major contract，and\n\
declarer's side holds an AJ tenace in one side suit (with East likely\n\
holding the Q) plus solid honors (AK or AKQ) in another side suit so a\n\
strip is feasible.\n\
\n\
The teaching pattern: strip the side suits where you have winners，then\n\
throw East in (typically with a heart or club) and force East to lead\n\
into your tenace. This converts a 50% finesse into a 100% endplay.\n\
\n\
Things to think about:\n\
• Count your losers; if a finesse can be avoided，look for a throw-in.\n\
• Strip the safe exits BEFORE the throw-in. Once East is in，every lead\n\
  helps you.\n\
• The thrown-in opponent should be the one holding the Q of your tenace\n\
  suit.\n\
\n\
Reference: https://www.bridgebum.com/endplay.php\n\
%FoundEndplay%,backgroundColor=lightpink
